              "media": {
                "id": "fs-id1626927",
                "alt": "The image on the left shows a spherical lipid bilayer, shown as a half sphere whose surface is covered in the spherical polar heads, and thin, strandlike tails extend inward.  In the core of the sphere is another half sphere, with the same anatomy but with the polar heads facing inward and the strandlike tails facing out toward the tails of the outer layer. The image on the right shows a smaller sphere that has a single lipid layer only, with the spherical heads facing outward. The image at the bottom shows a lipid bilayer sheet; whose polar heads form the upper and lower surfaces, with tails extending toward each other in the middle.",
